					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That depends on how fast the CHR RAM/ROM in the cartridge (and the mapper, if it has a PA12- or PA13-triggered interval timer) can react to three different PPUs all trying to read it. In addition, if you think 64K isn't enough for all the graphics you want to show on Super NES, imagine how small 8K will feel because there's no way to assign different CHR banks to different PPUs.</div>

