				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In NES games the multiplexor will be turned off.  As for clock speed, the multiplexor will be clocked at 64Mhz and accesses memory every 8 cycles.  The multiplexor would also divide it's clock speed by 3 to get the 21Mhz clock to power the 3 PPUs.  For ROM size, we can hook up a couple of the EXT pins to the address bus.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

