					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">MMC3, by comparison, was popular due to commercial interest. It's only natural that it wouldn't have the same post-market value outside reproduction and hacks. It just doesn't offer features that are interesting or convenient enough.</div><br /><br />I said MMC3 scale, meaning finely banked CHR, scanline counter, etc.  There are only a couple homebrews which utilize these types of features regardless if the mapper is interfaced in MMC3 fashion or not.  Those features do have post-market value, even if you don't understand/see it.  You talk about wanting parallax scrolling, but these &quot;uninteresting features of the MMC3&quot; are the features that permit parallax scrolling on the NES.</div>

					
